  "prompt": "How much of Google's mobile revenue comes from apps versus mobile search in browsers and the mobile web?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, Google has not publicly detailed the specific breakdown of its mobile revenue between apps and mobile search in browsers or the mobile web. However, it is widely understood that a significant portion of Google's mobile revenue comes from advertising, primarily through mobile search ads and in-app ads.\n\nMobile advertising has been a strong growth area for Google, with search ads in mobile browsers being a major contributor. Additionally, app-based ads, particularly through platforms like AdMob, also play a crucial role in their overall mobile revenue strategy.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, I recommend checking Google's annual financial reports or their parent company, Alphabet's, earnings reports, as they can provide insights into their revenue streams.",
